The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 3: Finance minister P. Chidambaram will meet the captains of Indian industry on July 5 to find ways to remove hurdles to achieve a 12 per cent growth in the manufacturing sector. The meeting, deferred thrice, is being held with the apex industry associations to deliberate on the ways and means of achieving the targeted growth rate in the manufacturing sector and to move on to a double-digit GDP growth.

 New Delhi, July 3: The government today notified a three-month extension sought by the department of telecommunications to ensure compliance of conditions regarding the increase in FDI cap in the telecom sector to 74 per cent from 49 per cent. 

 Mumbai, July 3: The Reserve Bank of India has issued draft guidelines which state that banks should identify their major sources of risk and carry out stress tests that are appropriate to them. The move is part of the RBI?s efforts to strengthen risk management practices in banks.

 Mumbai, July 3: Zee Telefilms? shareholders will meet on July 25 to consider the demerger of its business units into various companies. 

 Kuala Lumpur, July 3: Asia Pacific Breweries (APB) has joined hands with the Jaipuria group to set up its second brewery in India at a cost of $15 million.




